        <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
            <p>North Star Woolen Mill, Minneapolis; Lima, Ohio; Sanford, ME. Woolen mill founded in
                1864. Minneapolis operation closed in 1950 and business centered in Lima. In 1956,
                moved from Lima to Sanford. It merged with Maine Spinning Co. in 1959.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
            <p>Records include stockholders' ledger, 1941-1959; annual financial statements,
                1950-1954; articles of incorporation, as amended by typescript, 1945, 1949, 1951,
                1953 (gift of W.G. Northrup, Portsmouth, NH, June 1963); minutes, 1953-1958, of
                directors' &amp; stockholders' meetings; and correspondence.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <custodhist encodinganalog="MARC 582">
            <p>American Textile History Museum Collection, gift of Ames Stevens.</p>
        </custodhist>
